%N A395441 Squares visited by five knights, all starting on square 1, when moving on a square-spiral numbered board and always moving to the lowest available unvisited square.
%C A395441 All five knights, numbered 1..5, start at square one, and each moves in turn to the lowest available unvisited square, starting with the lowest numbered knight.
%C A395441 The sequence is finite - knight 2 is trapped on square 2768 after visiting 570 squares, knight 3 is trapped on square 4129 after visiting 809 squares, knight 5 is trapped on square 3799 after visiting 1155 squares, knight 1 is trapped on square 5876 after visiting 1268 squares, and knight 4 is trapped on square 10535 after visiting 6209 squares, giving a total of 10007 visited squares.
%H A395441 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A395441/b395441.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10007</a>
%H A395441 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A395441/a395441.png">Image of the knights' paths</a>. The knights' paths are colored red, yellow, green, blue and indigo, the final squares for knights 1, 2, 3 and 5 are colored yellow, and the final square for knight 4 is colored red.
